news.title: Bengaluru to add 25 million sq ft of new office supply in H2 FY27: ICRA
news.para: Bengaluru's office market is set for substantial growth. Over 25 million sq ft of new office space is expected in the latter half of FY27. Occupancy levels are projected to climb to over 92% by March 2027.

news.title: Sans master plan, Gaya fast becoming a concrete jungle
news.para: Gaya's growth is in limbo, hindered by an aging master plan from the 1960s that has long outlived its usefulness. This unbridled expansion has resulted in significant gaps in vital services for the community. A revitalizing new plan is on the horizon, but the wait extends to another year, alongside a distinct strategy for Bodh Gaya.

news.title: HDFC Capital commits ₹20 crore to Brigade Enterprises & Gruhas Proptech's Earth Fund
news.para: HDFC Capital has teamed up with Brigade Enterprises and Gruhas PropTech LLP, opting for a strategic minority stake in Zoiros Projects. Additionally, they are channeling ₹20 crore into the Earth Fund.

news.title: Hyderabad: GHMC expansion plan likely to double wards of civic body to 300
news.para: Hyderabad's municipal body is set for a significant expansion, potentially doubling its wards to nearly 300 and covering over 2,000 sq km with the proposed merger of 27 municipalities. This move would make GHMC India's largest municipal body by geographical spread and the largest elected one.

news.title: ED attaches over five lakh sq meters properties across three prime areas in North Goa
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) in Panaji has provisionally attached 19 Goan properties worth Rs 1,268.6 crore, suspected to be acquired through forged land documents. This action is part of an ongoing investigation into alleged land grab cases, with Shivshankar Mayekar identified as a key conspirator.

news.title: Ghaziabad civic body extends property tax rebate deadline till December 31
news.para: Ghaziabad municipal corporation has extended the property tax rebate deadline to December 31. Property owners can now avail a 20% rebate. This extension offers relief to consumers facing increased property tax. The civic body aims to collect 80% of its Rs 600 crore target for FY 2025-26. A case regarding the tax hike is pending in the Allahabad High Court.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: Handover of plots in Vasudev Vihar delayed as buyers await development
news.para: Buyers who secured plots in Bhubaneswar's Vasudev Vihar scheme are grappling with prolonged delays, with the Odisha State Housing Board still lagging in development two years post-booking closure. Promised infrastructure remains incomplete, and many of these frustrated buyers, mainly retired government officials, find themselves burdened by loan interests.

news.title: Odisha REAT upholds homebuyers’ rights in real estate dispute
news.para: Odisha Real Estate Appellate Tribunal has dismissed a public sector bank's plea to auction a stalled housing project. The tribunal ruled the bank, after taking possession under SARFAESI Act, stepped into the promoter's shoes and must cooperate in project completion. Buyers, who invested over a decade ago, expressed relief.

news.title: Mohali: 10-year wait ends, Punjab RERA orders developer to deliver delayed SCO unit
news.para: Buyers in Mohali have finally received a decade-long awaited victory as RERA Punjab ordered a developer to hand over possession of a commercial SCO.  Despite paying full price and completing formalities for unit 178 in High Plaza Market, possession was denied. The authority ruled in favor of the buyers, mandating possession within three months and compensation for the extensive delay.

news.title: NCLT dismisses Chronos Properties' ₹1,080 crore bid for IL&FS flagship BKC property
news.para: In a significant ruling, the National Company Law Tribunal dismissed Chronos Properties' bid of Rs 1,080 crore for the coveted Bandra Kurla Complex, as held by IL&FS. The tribunal upheld IL&FS's right to modify the bid amount, prompting Chronos to provide a performance guarantee within the next month. Previously, IL&FS had attempted to withdraw the bid, citing various compliance issues.

news.title: UK lenders approve more mortgages than expected in October, consumer lending cools
news.para: In an unexpected twist, UK mortgage approvals in October surpassed projections, overcoming budget apprehensions that loomed over the market. Although consumer borrowing has taken a breather, the small dip in mortgage approvals demonstrates a sturdy housing landscape amid fears of tax increases and policy uncertainties.

news.title: Bombay HC rejects challenge to WeWork India IPO, imposes ₹1 lakh cost
news.para: The Bombay High Court dismissed two petitions seeking to block WeWork India's IPO, imposed a Rs 1 lakh cost on one petitioner, and upheld SEBI's regulatory decisions. The Court noted that disclosures were made as required and that investors had shown strong interest in the oversubscribed issue.

news.title: Wakefit to float IPO on December 8; eyes ₹1,400 crore
news.para: Wakefit Innovations Ltd is set to launch its IPO on December 8, targeting Rs 1,400 crore. The IPO features a fresh issuance alongside an offer-for-sale. Proceeds from this venture will be utilized for new store openings, advanced machinery, and comprehensive marketing strategies.

news.title: Sushmita Sen, mother buy two apartments worth ₹16.89 crore in Mumbai
news.para: Sushmita Sen' and her mother have acquired two luxury apartments in Mumbai's Goregaon East. The properties in Elysian by Oberoi Realty were bought for a combined ₹16.89 crore. Both deals were registered in November 2025.

news.title: Delhi: Vasant Kunj residents protest against nod for group housing project on Morphological Ridge
news.para: Residents of B-1, Vasant Kunj, protested at Jantar Mantar against a group housing project approved for the Morphological Ridge. Despite clearances from multiple authorities, protestors argue the construction of three 10-storey luxury towers violates norms and endangers Delhi's green lungs. They claim statutory safeguards for citizens and the Ridge were ignored.

news.title: Maharashtra govt seeks SRA’s response on affordable housing for first-floor slum residents
news.para: Maharashtra government is seeking a report from SRA on making first-floor slum dwellers eligible for free/affordable housing. The finance department is assessing the potential financial burden on the state if developers receive concessions. This move, pushed by BJP, could influence upcoming BMC polls by potentially benefiting a significant population previously excluded from SRA schemes.

news.title: ED accuses Experion Developers of misusing IBC rules in land deal
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate has accused Experion Developers of misusing the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code. The agency claims Experion improperly acquired land in Gurugram's Sector 62. Experion allegedly manipulated the committee of creditors to approve a resolution plan. The ED has asked the National Company Law Tribunal to recall its order. Experion denies the allegations, stating debt assignments were legitimate.

news.title: Japanese property giants deepen their push into a booming Indian market
news.para: Japanese property giants are setting their sights on India, captivated by soaring rental prices and cost-effective construction. Notable players like Mitsui Fudosan and Sumitomo Realty are making hefty investments as they explore new ventures in office, retail, and hospitality sectors.

news.title: Registration of properties in Mumbai region up 20% in November at 12,219 units
news.para: Mumbai's property market experienced a remarkable surge in November. The volume of registered real estate soared by 20% compared to last year, marking the highest level for November since 2013. Additionally, stamp duty revenues enjoyed a substantial boost.

news.title: Nagpur civic body inks ₹129 crore deal to redevelop Sokta Bhavan
news.para: Nagpur Municipal Corporation has finalized a Rs129 crore deal to redevelop the dilapidated Sokta Bhavan into a modern commercial complex and Citizen Facilitation Centre. Awarded on a DBFOS basis, this project marks a significant boost to the civic body's non-tax revenue after multiple failed attempts to attract bidders.
